//! The PNG renderer needs actual glyph shapes, not Unicode code points,
//! so it carries the classic IBM VGA 8x16 text-mode font: 256 glyphs
//! indexed directly by CP437 byte, each 16 rows of 8 horizontal pixels
//! (bit 7 = leftmost column, bit 0 = rightmost). This is the same ROM
//! font DOS displayed, so box-drawing, blocks, and shading all render
//! faithfully. The bitmap is a de-facto public-domain typeface.

